    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras face a high-variance slate today, anchored by **Yordan Alvarez** (72.47) and **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (63.51). **Yordan Alvarez** is our clear top offensive engine; despite a neutral park adjustment, his elite xwOBA of 0.393 against a vulnerable Lorenzen keeps his floor remarkably high. Conversely, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** earns a \"Strong\" start designation largely due to an aggressive dynamic platoon edge and wind conditions, which outweigh the drag of his #8 spot in the order and the presence of an elite opposing catcher. **Caleb Durbin** also remains a focal point for our SB-weighted strategy, benefiting from a prime #2 lineup position and a favorable matchup against Abel to yield a 61.94 efficiency score.\n\nRisks abound across the diamond, particularly with our middle infield and bench management. **Chase Meidroth** (53.69) and **Junior Caminero** (61.03) are both flagged with a 39% rain risk in their respective matchups against tough lefties. **Victor Scott II** represents our most difficult bench decision, failing to crack the starting nine with a score of 39.65. While his elite sprint speed is a priority for us, his current plate discipline profile combined with a poor platoon matchup against Cantillo ultimately forced him below the 40.0 \"Zebras Floor\" threshold. We are monitoring **Josh Smith** and **Hyeseong Kim** closely, as both are currently slated based on assumed #7 and #9 spots in lineups that have yet to be finalized; should their order drop further, their efficiency scores\u2014already hovering near the margin\u2014could necessitate a roster pivot to preserve game caps.",
